I thought my problem is protobuf version. I reinstalled my system and built pytorch, torchision in anaconda from source, then I built caffe2 from source into system folder ,like "/usr/local" not using anaconda python, finally i built onnx from source instead of pip installation and pip install onnx-caffe2 tool to convert pytorch model to caffe2 model.

> Did you run git submodule update --init --recursive right before you built Caffe2?
> Did you install ONNX separately from source?
> What were the commands you used to build Caffe2 and what was the

I thought my problem is protobuf version. I reinstalled my system and built pytorch, torchision in anaconda from source, then I built caffe2 from source into system folder ,like "/usr/local" not using anaconda python, finally i built onnx from source instead of pip installation and pip install onnx-caffe2 tool to convert pytorch model to caffe2 model.
I solved it through this way.
